I"À<div class="p">Immortal day! the scrub-faced freshman sings</div>
<div class="p">With treble rapture for ethereal things;</div>
<div class="p">His beaming face confesses all afire</div>
<div class="p">A mind that whiffs and traces prior and prior.</div>
<div class="p">The healthy, wholesome innocence of youth</div>
<div class="p">Strains after the eternal flame of truth,</div>
<div class="p">Fair proof the dotage of the cultured world</div>
<div class="p">Has tender leaflets yet by Spring unfurled.</div>
<div class="p">With quivering passion, sedulous for lore,</div>
<div class="p">Affections groping for themes more and more,</div>
<div class="p">With nimble fingers grasping office tools,
<div class="p">Pride's passport through the binder-happy schools,
<div class="p">Our wide-eyed Freshman ogles trembling spheres</div>
<div class="p">Of things unknown with mingled hopes and fears.</div>
<div class="p">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Tucked under his spaghetti arms, behold</div>
<div class="p">The notebooks, note-full, leaf on leaf of gold.</div>
<div class="p">No gentle hint warns him from scribbling notes</div>
<div class="p">Of heady notions and pertaining quotes,</div>
<div class="p">Which pile and pile before he has a class,</div>
<div class="p">And skyward soar a thousand miles, alas.</div>
<div class="p">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; The Dawn's rose-fingers signal Freshman's day,</div>
<div class="p">With weary but with grateful Freshman fay,</div>
<div class="p">From Homer's study through the summer long,</div>
<div class="p">He grits his teeth and vows not to be wrong.</div>
<div class="p">The dormitory's gates of learning ope,</div>
<div class="p">He enters with an intellect and soap.</div>
<div class="p">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Commence the universal day of Whirl,</div>
<div class="p">Alike enjoyed by costumed boy and girl.</div>
<div class="p">The instant intimates across the hall,</div>
<div class="p">Where girls wait for their friends to take the fall;</div>
