<div class="p">With baby faces talk as good as ten!</div>
<div class="p">The snubbing upperclassmen, swarm-bound, pass</div>
<div class="p">From rooms when Freshmen enter for a class,</div>
<div class="p">And mutter as they go, "Freshmen," with wit</div>
<div class="p">Three years bestows, they laugh and go, the hit
<div class="p">O'erawed gapes where the lampoon tasted flesh,
<div class="p">His soul yearns for a terrible egress.
<div class="p">Impassioned bureaucrats discourse while meeting,
<div class="p">Their droning, never-ending themes repeating:
<div class="p">The calendar: "Resilience in College"â€”
<div class="p">One needs resilience to bear this knowledge!
<div class="p">And thousand scheduled suchlike hours glad hearts
<div class="p">That feared to find exacting liberal arts.
<div class="p">Vainglorious administrators proud</div>
<div class="p">Of their one office that bears wind and cloud,</div>
<div class="p">Bestride, than wind or tide a greater force
<div class="p">Of nature, with a driving, roaring course
<div class="p">That over-sweeping mauls its jaw-bound catch,
<div class="p">A bureaucratic wave of highest pitch.
<div class="p">The slouching Freshmen with their heads of hair</div>
<div class="p">Who mutter awkwardly on every stair;</div>
<div class="p">The greasy long-haired intellectual chaps</div>
